==Russian==

===Etymology===
For individual etymologies, see the words: [[в#Russian|в]] [[Тула#Russian|Тулу]] [[с#Russian|со]] [[свой|своим]] [[самовар|самоваром]]. The phrase derives from the fact that [[w:Tula|Tula]] is well known for [[samovar]]s. The phrase was coined by [[w:Chekhov|Chekhov]].

===Idiom===
'''в Тулу со своим самоваром''' (v Túlu so svoím samovárom)

# do something that is not needed (''literally:'' [going] to [[w:Tula|Tula]] with your own [[samovar]]); see [[owls to Athens]] and [[coals to Newcastle]]
#*И коллеги удивленно пожимают плечами: В Тулу со своим самоваром? [http://www.intertravel.ru/sovet/sovet24.php]
#**''And the colleagues shrug their shoulders: to Tula with the samovar?''

